HEADWORD: Maledicent
<hw>Mal`e*di"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>maledicens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>maledicere</ets> to speak ill;
<ets>male</ets> ill + <ets>dicere</ets> to say, speak. See
<er>Malice</er>, and <er>Diction</er>.]</ety> <def>Speaking
reproachfully; slanderous.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir E.
Sandys.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maledict</ent>⟦br⟧
